                        <a href="#" class="ing">5)	Search Engine Optimization</a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="question4" class="panel-collapse collapse" style="height: 0px;">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
                            Getting high rankings on Google is a must for your ecommerce site, therefor SEO is an important marketing strategy to implement so you are not missing out on the clicks that lead to potential sales. The better your click-through-rate (CTR) the higher your position will be on the search engine. This will prevent you from loosing out on brand impressions, clicks and sales.
                            <br />To have a successful CTR you must ensure you have done the correct keyword research, such as finding the best keywords for your homepage and products page. Use highly relevant keywords to your brand. And more importantly research into the keyword searches that are working well for your competitors.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

